Pt. has chronic CHF , w/ flares approximately every 6 months. Her baseline weight is 130-135 lbs , and she follows daily weights at home. Baseline exercise tolerance is 5 flights of stairs. Over the past 5 days , she noticed increased weight ( 1 lb/d x 5d ) , slight incr. SOB , and some presacral edema. On night before admission , she awoke from sleep SOB , and had to sleep sitting upright for remainder of night. No clear dietary indiscretion; no immediately recent med change , but has not been on ARB since stroke in order to keep BP higher. On exam , afebrile , JVP 12 cm , lungs wet 1/2 way up w/ dullness at both bases. CK , TnI negative x 3; TSH normal; Labs notable for HCt of 30% ( baseline = 40% ). Diuresed 1L over first night , goal diuresis an additional 1-2L on HD#2. Added back ARB 7/24 and plan to discharge home with slightly higher Lasix dose until weight down to ~130lbs. Check INR Wed 3/3 with goal 2-3 and follow up w/ Dr. Ellenbogen ADDITIONAL COMMENTS: Blood draw for INR check Wednesday and call results in to Dr. Bayes for Coumadin adjustment. Follow daily weights.
